ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC FORMAT <option(s)>;
      EXCLUDE entry(s);  
      INVALUE <$>name <(informat-option(s))> value-range-set(s);  
      PICTURE name <(format-option(s))> value-range-set-1 <(picture-1-option(s) )> <...value-range-set-n <(picture-n-option(s))>>;  
      SELECT entry(s);  
      VALUE <$>name <(format-option(s))> value-range-set(s);  

The FORMAT procedure enables you to define your own informats and formats for variables. 
In addition, you can print the parts of a catalog that contain informats or formats, store 
descriptions of informats or formats in a SAS data set, and use a SAS data set to create 
informats or formats.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PICTURE name <(format-option(s))> <value-range-set-1 <(picture-1-option(s) )> 
      <...value-range-set-n <(picture-n-option(s))>>>; 

Creates a template for printing numbers.
